##Shelter Nurse: leading the patients to exercise is also our happiest time

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Duan Yanchao is a reporter for the paper, and Wang Sali is an intern

"When I first arrived at Jiangxia District's Shelter Hospital, my colleagues and I felt a bit overwhelmed by the intense work of the daily rotation, and then things gradually improved and the medical team gradually returned to normal working conditions, " he said on February 24, li Zhenpeng, a member of the Chinese medical team of the state (Henan) and a nurse in the Department of Suction Medicine at the First Affiliated Hospital of Henan University of Chinese Medicine, told thepaper.cn that the situation is getting better and better, and everyone's confidence in overcoming the epidemic has doubled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo courtesy of Li Zhenpeng in the shelter hospital

Li Zhenpeng said that when the epidemic is over, the first thing is to report a safe family.

Li Zhenpeng's anti-epidemic diary of 24 February:

Today is the 15th day of arrival in Wuhan and the 11th day of arrival in Jiangxia District's Shelter Hospital in Wuhan. From the first night shift on February 14 to the second break today, I have worked nine consecutive night shifts.

Working and living in a series of upside-down night shifts is hard work, but what is all this hard work when you consider that so many patients have not recovered? The main purpose of our journey is to win the battle against the plague. I think, under our joint efforts, will certainly obtain the final victory, Wuhan refuels! We're always here!

All say that Wuhan's Cherry Blossom is very good-looking, there are many delicious food, I had wanted to come to Wuhan to play. Unexpectedly, the first time to Wuhan, is Emergency Assistance Wuhan anti-epidemic, shelter densely packed beds, is all the scenery.

On February 10,33 members of our medical team came to Jiangxia District. After recuperation and training, they began to work on February 14. My first night shift was from 2 a.m. to 8 a.m.

I still remember going to work, the wind and rain, I and my teammates on the bus, although there is some inner tension, but we encourage each other, support, we firmly believe in the fight into the epidemic.

At present, our team has fully managed the 86 beds, I as night shift (4:00 a.m. to 10:00 a.m.) care team leader, there will usually be 3-4 medical care for these patients, the workload is still relatively large. Although the patients in the shelter hospital are mostly mild patients, there are individual changes in the condition, more serious. So, in addition to completing our shift work, we need to closely observe the changes in these patients, ready to respond. Because of continuous work, long-term wear masks, goggles, we have been pressed into the face of deep marks, as well as colleagues have worn the skin bridge of the nose. But the "loveliest" never complained.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Zhenpeng (first left) and three colleagues

I was the First Affiliated Hospital of Henan University of Traditional Chinese Medicine Suction medical earth, from 2015 to date, has not participated in the work of such a fight against the epidemic. From the outbreak of the epidemic, the initiative to ask for war, confirmation, training and assessment, to Wuhan, into the fight, I feel I learned a lot, but also a lot of growth.

These days, there are hard, touching, harvest, happy, very tired, but also very full. We work six hours a day, but we have to get up an hour and a half earlier to get supplies and to go, because we have to take the shuttle bus, and we have to wear protective clothing, and then we have to take off the protective clothing and take the shuttle bus for an hour and a half after that. Wearing a protective suit for six hours, can not eat, drink, go to the toilet, and covered in special tight, breathing is not smooth, sweating, body sometimes itching is not scratching, these are very uncomfortable. In the work, give the patient measure vital signs, hair medicine, hair rice, more will be a lot of sweating, the body will be particularly uncomfortable. But we all overcame these difficulties and adapted to it.

In the ward, ninety per cent of the patients are suffering from mild illness. In addition to treatment, we will also lead the patients to practice Baduanjin, Meridians and collaterals beating, Taijiquan and dancing, in order to enrich everyone's life, promote everyone's physical exercise, and enhance their resistance, and the patients love it. These are the times when we're happiest.

Of course, there are some special cases of patients, their families died in the epidemic, the mood is very depressed. Some patients are depressed emotionally, some patients'whole families are living in the different ward of the Shelter Hospital, the heart is always on tenterhooks, etc. . These patients, we need to pay attention to their psychological status, communicate with them, guide them, encourage them to face the epidemic, and ultimately overcome it.

Many patients in the ward are very cooperative with us, also understand us, will take the initiative to help us, medicine, organization, exercise together, always transfer positive energy, let us very moved. We often hear patients say, "thank you for coming to support Wuhan, you have worked hard, " and so on, which makes me very touched, but also feel more responsible. I often tell myself in silence, do not break the epidemic not to return!

Before Wuhan, my family, friends are very worried, repeatedly told me to do a good job of protection, but they did not say Wuhan dangerous you do not go, because they understand me. As a paramedic, it's my responsibility. When I choose this path, I should have such courage and responsibility. I will be there, and I will be back, and I assure them that this plague will continue for some time to come, but in the end, victory will be ours.

If you are dressed in white, you will not fail it. The weather in Wuhan is getting warmer and the sun is shining, and I think in a month or so the Cherry Blossoms will be gone.

COME ON, Wuhan! Come on, cutest people!

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
